From: Carl Joakim Damsleth <kim@damsleth.com>
Subject: [PATCH] pmdomain: apple: encode T6041 raw-boot PMGR quirks

T6041 raw boot leaves core firmware resources active, and two external-display
CPU domains reject the generic AUTO_ENABLE write. The exact minimum was
isolated on a T6040 J614s with the full 214-domain hierarchy: preserve domains
that firmware left active, skip auto-enable only for dispext0_cpu and
dispext1_cpu, and leave the separately inaccessible disp_cpu disabled in DT.

Key that behavior from the existing T6041 compatible instead of temporary
bring-up properties. Keep property handling for experiment reproduction and
older trees.

Also document the already-used T6041 PMGR compatibles in the bindings.

diff --git a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/arm/apple/apple,pmgr.yaml b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/arm/apple/apple,pmgr.yaml
--- a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/arm/apple/apple,pmgr.yaml
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/arm/apple/apple,pmgr.yaml
@@ -48,6 +48,7 @@ properties:
           - enum:
               - apple,t6020-pmgr
               - apple,t8122-pmgr
+              - apple,t6041-pmgr
           - const: apple,t8103-pmgr
           - const: syscon
           - const: simple-mfd
diff --git a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/power/apple,pmgr-pwrstate.yaml b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/power/apple,pmgr-pwrstate.yaml
--- a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/power/apple,pmgr-pwrstate.yaml
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/power/apple,pmgr-pwrstate.yaml
@@ -47,6 +47,7 @@ properties:
           - enum:
               - apple,t6020-pmgr-pwrstate
               - apple,t8122-pmgr-pwrstate
+              - apple,t6041-pmgr-pwrstate
           - const: apple,t8103-pmgr-pwrstate
 
   reg:
diff --git a/drivers/pmdomain/apple/pmgr-pwrstate.c b/drivers/pmdomain/apple/pmgr-pwrstate.c
--- a/drivers/pmdomain/apple/pmgr-pwrstate.c
+++ b/drivers/pmdomain/apple/pmgr-pwrstate.c
@@ -213,7 +213,6 @@ static int apple_pmgr_ps_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
 	ps->dev = dev;
-	ps->skip_auto_enable = of_property_read_bool(node, "apple,skip-auto-enable");
 	ps->regmap = regmap;
 
 	ret = of_property_read_string(node, "label", &name);
@@ -222,6 +221,13 @@ static int apple_pmgr_ps_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		return ret;
 	}
 
+	/* T6041 raw boot firmware locks auto-PM on the display CPU domains. */
+	ps->skip_auto_enable =
+		of_property_read_bool(node, "apple,skip-auto-enable") ||
+		(of_device_is_compatible(node, "apple,t6041-pmgr-pwrstate") &&
+		 (!strcmp(name, "dispext0_cpu") ||
+		  !strcmp(name, "dispext1_cpu")));
+
 	ret = of_property_read_u32(node, "reg", &ps->offset);
 	if (ret < 0) {
 		dev_err(dev, "missing reg property\n");
@@ -239,7 +245,11 @@ static int apple_pmgr_ps_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 				   FIELD_PREP(APPLE_PMGR_PS_MIN, ps->min_state));
 
 	active = apple_pmgr_ps_is_active(ps);
-	if (active && of_property_read_bool(node->parent, "apple,preserve-active"))
+	/*
+	 * T6041 raw boot has no earlier OS stage to quiesce firmware-owned domains.
+	 */
+	if (active && (of_property_read_bool(node->parent, "apple,preserve-active") ||
+		       of_device_is_compatible(node, "apple,t6041-pmgr-pwrstate")))
 		ps->genpd.flags |= GENPD_FLAG_ALWAYS_ON;
 
 	if (of_property_read_bool(node, "apple,always-on")) {
